caption: Thank you for addressing my concern. I'm changing my review to 5 stars because your food is absolutely delicious and has amazing  value for the price. I hope one day you're able to bring back the fresh stuff, I would happily pay extra for it.

This place was so good! We got three of the vegetarian rolls (V3, secret garden, shitake tempura). Very unique flavors, almost a sweet/umami combo. One of the rolls was warm. Pretty filling and SOOOOO good. We also loved the gyoza and got the match cheesecake which was to die for. Only thing that was just okay was the philly roll. We will definitely be back!

My husband and I received a special treat for #valentinesday  The Lover  Maki from @seadogsushibar A heart-shaped maki filled with spicy smoked salmon, squash tempura, and masago, wrapped in tuna  So fresh and delicious!  They are currently open for curbside pick up and delivery. They offer lots of  delicious Japanese sushi.  Thanks @chicagofoodiegirl and @seadogsushibar for the delicious treat!  It's easy to see why they are a four time Michelin recommended restaurant.  The food is just that good!  Do yourself a favor and try them today!

This is my second time getting takeout from here and and was so impressed by the quality, again. Really fresh, large pieces of fish in the maki. I loved the yellowtail scallion (one of my favorites) and the miso soup was fantastic. I also had a roll with torched white tuna, unagi, and black masago and it was awesome. Sushi has been hit or miss for me all over the city for delivery/takeout over the past 10 years, but this is a small business that pays attention to detail.
Ordered delivery today. Food came early. Gyoza is pretty standard wherever you go but there’s a sauce they use that is absolutely delicious. Fish was fresh. Will definitely order again.
Cozy basement restaurant - don't let that discourage you. Freshest ingredients!
Really cute patio and a reasonable price.
This place is always the best with the fresh ingredients and taste through different sushi option. Great prices for the quality&taste as well. No better place around!!!

Monday’s are super moist and juicy.   Spicy tuna is delicious as well as avocado rolls. Spicy miso soup is yum! All other places thus far I’ve gotten sick but not here and we order a lot. Hope this helps!!

They have a nice patio for outdoor seating but staff sat people right next to us even though many other options available.  This is byob but we wish we had known this when making reservations.   We were not impressed with our selections especially one with sweet potato that didn't work.

Excellent experience here and we plan on returning often ! You must try the spooky Maki, and the sea monster! And the green machine .. oh, and the sushi flight! Heck, try it all! Great service and great menu!
Exceptional and tasty food, I like the ambience the place has, and the cashiers were super nice. Will definitely visit here next time.
Great sushi in an awesome setting! Will def be back soon.
Awesome place. Best sushi in the cittern. DO NOT let the small entrance and stairway to the basement restaurant scare you away.  You'll live the foods down the vibe.

I'm convinced the higher rated reviews are either people drunkenly remembering their experience here as great or being overpowered by the live DJ. Sometimes a mix of the two, which, fair play, was pretty Damn good. That's not what I'm here for, I'm here to comment on the food.
This sushi place are not as good as before, need to  improve little more than before.
Long wait even after ordering ahead of time for pickup.
Typically love the sushi here but the green river roll was terrible. I physically couldn't eat it!
Love this place...its the best sushi in town
Excellent sushi! Attentive service! Amazing quiet patio with intimate white lights. We had a great date night here. Brought our own bottle of wine and enjoyed our time!
Had a very good experience here with my kids. The food comes out rapidly and the service is just awesome. Prices are reasonable.
Awesome place to have some food when in a hurry. Their customer service is fast, prices are convenient, awesome atmosphere. Will come visit again
We've been here several times, the food is consistently excellent, the rolls are inventive and delicious, and we always leave uncomfortably full.
Extraordinary environment and super welcoming service. The meals were crisp and delightful. Will easily recommend this spot to my friends. Convenient prices and generous portions. Great job.

I've dined in several times and also ordered for delivery. Either options gives you very delicious rolls and sushi. They suffer greatly  in service. My delivery took an hour and half to arrive, when I was given an estimate of no more than an hour. Called the restuarant twice to inquire after the initial hour, to be told it was on it's way. Did finally receive the order, no explanation as to the delay. The food is good, but you gotta decide if it's worth the wait (even when dining in). Also, the portion sizes seem to have shrunk, my most recent delivery has a signature maki with only 6 small rolls. I used to love this place, but have had to update my rating with the declining experiences.
We have been repeat customers for over 2 years now. Always consistent, good quality delicious sushi.
Great food and service!
Fresh, delicious and really lovely sushi. I also enjoyed the spicy miso and the spicier than average wasabi - yum.

My girlfriend and I ordered sushi for pickup this past weekend. She has a shellfish allergy so we specifically asked to prepare her food in a new area. After taking one bite of her tuna roll it was clear that there was cross contamination and she had an allergic reaction and needed to go to the hospital. Will never recommend to anyone, especially those with food allergies.
Had a very good experience in this spot with my daughter. The food came quickly and the customer service is just awesome. Prices are convenient.
Such a good sushi place. So so fresh. Amazing prices as well - highly recommended!

Whenever we're in the city the debate comes up for if we should come to Seadog for sushi since we love it so much. Great food that is fairly prices and Everytime we've been there the staff has been super friendly.

The food is good. The back room is horribly, horribly loud and they pack so many tables in that we were unable to sit comfortably and enjoy our meal, the servers were constantly bumping into us.. don't go here on a weekend and it should be great
Fantastic sushi
Had a good experience here with my wife. The food comes rapidly and the service is just great. Prices are convenient.
This spot is excellent! Good rates, big dishes and the staff members are constantly kind.
It's beautiful, it's delicious, there are options for any kind of diet. This place is the best of its kind for miles around.

Mixed review here. Used to be a local favorite (10years ago when we lived in the neighborhood). Sushi quality seems to have dropped. Overcompensating for lower quality fish with over-saucing, over-mayo-ing, deep frying and cream cheesing. Super friendly staff. Beautiful low lighting. Love the BYOB.

two days ago was the first time in this fine restaurant. But It is no doubt not the last time. We had great time with the generous service, with the magnificent cooking and booze and with the friendly payment. We will definitely go back there again.

Really great little sushi place. All the rolls and food were good, especially for the price. And speaking of, BYOB with no corkage fee. The decor was really great and upscale and the service was good. That pushes this place to our new go to sushi place in wicker park.
Order something you don't recognize or that looks like you might not be interested in it. This place will surprise you and you'll be impressed. At least, that's how it goes for me when I'm there.

I purchased online the Spicy Ebi tempura roll. 1) Not your typical tempura batter, more like panko breading. 2) not the typical amount of pieces for a maki roll. 4 total pieces in my take out box. I wasn’t able to check when I was handed my bag. When I did look, I was shocked to see only 4 pieces. The price paid was not worth what I ordered.
Fantastic service. What a great date spot. Thank you for the experience.

Went here for lunch on a Sunday, had lots of open seating. We tried the seaweed salad which was great, got a free sweet potato tempura with yelp check in which was yummy. For maki rolls tried the volcano which was okay (not a fan of tempura in my maki rolls). However also tried the spooky roll which is a warm, spicy maki roll which was delicious! So much so that we ordered another one of em. Service was a bit slow considering only 3 tables were occupied and it took a good 20-30mins for our rolls to come hence 4star. Got free street parking outside which was nice too. Would recommend especially for the spooky roll! Happy eating!

Helpful waiters, friendly hosting, BYOB. Really good food! Great elevated romantic seat with great window seat. Perfect for mid-week date night, when they're not too busy and it's close to done pretty good night life spots for afterwards!
Very delicious!!! Great ambiance, as well as the service. We went on a Thursday night when it wasn’t that busy, and we were able to sit in the backyard patio. It’s BYOB!

Pros: Pretty cool place, sort of small and low key, for a date prob., deliver through 2rd party at least. And good food.  Cons: good location on division but hard to see on corner, Signage not super great. Usually under staffed anf therefore slow service. There's plenty of other sushi shops around, I would compare others 1st (rip city sushi burrito.
Excellent sushi in Wicker Park, BYOB.

The service was extremely slow. We waited about a half hour for an appetizer and over an hour for four rolls. It was not very busy. When walking through the restaurant to the patio there was a strong unpleasant odor. The patio itself had a lot of trash blowing around napkins and cans from previous guests.  When we got the rolls themselves they were on the smaller side which is fine. However the flavor was not good. I will not be back.
It was great food!
Great prices and great tastes

Great sushi restaurant in Chicago! Very tasty and fresh sushi and fish! Offers all you can eat packages for family or party with friends! Very good service, staff friendly and helpful. Conveniently located near highway, right after exit. Prices are manageable for Chicago! Definitely would recommend it to try!!
Good Service

accidentally brought me the 1 order of wrong rolls (I almost ordered them anyway) so they let me keep them and brought me what I originally ordered, food incredibly good though and best vegetarian sushi place I've found

Might be good for a quick lunch spot. But I was there for dinner. Sushi was par for the course and it was kind of loud. It was kind of hard to talk to the people I was with. We were seated in the back and there wasn't much room to move around so I had to keep moving my seat. Server was good. Miso soup was good.
Love  Seadog Sushi! It's my favorite sushi restaurant in Chicago. Great food, great service.
Best sushi bar in chicago
Excellent saw selections, great service, amazing spicy miso soup!

The seadog sushi bar had freshly made sushi rolls that have unique constructions and ingridents. The location is bring your own alcohol so don't forget that. I definitly want to go back and try many other options from the menu as people around me had great looking dishes
I really enjoy this place for sushi. Very casual and great sushi. This time the service was really slow and we had drank all of our BYOB beverages and were not even through with dinner.
Extremely peaceful as well as a pleasant time to chat.
Food was good, but several items were added to my bill. Management was very helpful even after my visit to refund me for the items.
Excellent food and service

They have really fun maki rolls which are good. Maybe we went on a bad night but we waited an hour for our food. The sushi was not very good, too much fish on too little rice. The service wasn’t the best either and it was hard to get a hold of the waitstaff. The menu and overall vibe is good and judging by other reviews it seems we went there on an off night. Maybe we will try it again.
One of our favorite BYOB sushi places in Chicago. Quality is always top notch, cool atmosphere, and good prices. Subscribe to their email list for occasional deals
Great food and friendly staff with reasonable prices for the city. BYOB helps as well :)
Dragon roll was very small for the price and quality was low. Tempura was a heavy coating and more like a breading.

This is a great budget sushi joint. They are BYO, service is quick and they have plenty of space. What more do you need? We got a large sushimi and the volcano roll and it was exactly what we expected for the price. It gets quite crowded in the evenings so be sure to make reservations!
So far so good.  Fresh and delicious. One of the best sushi I've ever tried. I recommend this place. Good service and great atmosphere.
Good sushi overall. Friendly service and fast.
Very nice place, food was great
Love this place. One of my favorite spots for sushi in Chicago

I took off two stars because the food was bad enough that I wouldn't recommend it. My server was really nice and it had a really good atmosphere but the only thing that I ordered that was good was a traditional Japanese Maki. This could easily be a five-star spot if all you order is within that menu but I would not recommend any Americanized rolls that they offer or the non sushi dishes.
Generous portion sizes, especially with the spicy tuna hand roll. The yellow tail sashimi was delicious! Cool atmosphere as well.
I recommend the green goblin and the eel roll. Not a fan of the crab in the crusher though.
very good size, great taste, amazing price and BYOB which is great. Love it
The sushi variety is great. I can appreciate the not so typical variety so thats a plus.

I thought I would check this place out for a quick roll since I'm pretty new to the neighborhood and it's around the corner from my house.  I was pleasantly surprised by the service and overall experience. I was greeted at the door immediately and seated right away at the bar. Given water right off the bat and emptied it quickly since I was very thirsty and it was then refilled right away. Love it!  The server was on top of everything throughout the quick in and out experience. The sushi maker on the other side of the bar was pleasant and engaged with me.  The food was tasty and fresh. I got the Triple S and it was my first time having sweet potato in sushi. They even threw in a tempura sweet potato app for free for checking in on facebook! (Smart Social Move)  What drove me to write this review is that it wasn't just one person involved in my great first experience at Seadog, upon leaving I think 5 different people thanked me for coming in. Thank You Seadog Staff. I'll be back.
Different
BYOB. Very good but the small portions make it even more expensive for a meal.
High quality sushi , good atmosphere

Sushi at Seadog Sushi Bar is really delicious however the prices are high for the small portions they provide. Staff is limited to a few people and unfortunately are not very attentive. Yes this is a BYOB location however that does not make up for some of the shortcomings. The location is small and crowded as well so if you are thinking you can get a spacious table; aim for the outside seating.
Really nice nigiri. The cuts of fish were excellent. Spicy tuna roll could have been spicier. The green tea was better than most I've had.

The sushi here is so fresh and delicious, and their rolls are super creative and have amazing flavor profiles. Reasonably priced, BYOB, and while the service can be a bit slow because of how popular this place is, they're very nice and friendly.
Well it wasn't what  I expected to eat and expensive

Went here with my wife for my birthday. The sushi was fresh and delicious, the machi were wonderfully creative and the flavors well layered. The service was slow, but worth the wait. It’s BYOB, we brought along a bottle of Ryoshi Zake Junmai Ginjo. It paired very well with the entire meal. We will be back!
Great sushi!

Stumbled here by chance and had a wonderful experience. My group sat outside which was a large space with bistro lights. The Michelen recommended restaurant had amazing sashimi, we ordered the large sashimi platter and each cut was large, fresh, and delicious. It was BYOB (with no cork fee) which paired nicely with the summer heat. We ordered a few appetizers (sweet potato tempura, edamame, and gyzo) and had a lot of rolls, all of which were delicious and decent size. The dragon roll was a favorite among the group. Finished off dinner with matcha and mango mochi ice cream
Sea Monster is one of the delicious maki rolls that’s graced Chicago.
My favorite sushi place. After sampling sushi on both Coasts, and around Japan, I think I like Seadog maki most.
Always busy, but great sushi and awesome service! BYOB too :)
Expensive and not great service.
BYOB was nice. Sushi was standard, nothing to rave about. Service was fine. If you don’t like cramped spaces, don’t even bother here. Overall fine experience.
This spot can easily be dismissed because of location, but they have some fresh and tasty items!

This is a great place! It seems very cozy. It's byob , which is even better. I highly recommend the spicy miso soup. I had two bowls it was so good. I dined in with 2 other people and we ordered a couple of rolls. The spider roll, was so good. The rainbow king is equally as good. We loved the triple S. Overall I loved the sushi and the establishment. I will be back, as often as I can.
Cozy set up with awesome sushi
Very good Sushi place. Good price, great quality. It's also a bit small which makes it cozy. I 'll keep coming.
My boyfriend and myself have been going here for 5 years and its just getting better!
Very impressive sushi!
All of it was were on point especially the Volcano, Fried Scallops, Honey Crab.
Delicious food, small intimate atmosphere, good prices, and BYOB!

I’m a frequent customer here. The service is terrible - I never go in person because their service is too slow. When I call for delivery I’m often put on hold for several minutes before they hang up. However the food is really good, not too much rice and the fish is really fresh.
Great place with reasonable cost. BYOB
Great sushi place
BYOB! Sushi selection is great, atmosphere is dark and intimate in a good way. Love this place.
This place has a modern feel with delicious food. BYOB for all the people having a social night. And the miso soup is only $2 and oh so good.
Good  food.
Excellent neighborhood sushi spot with fresh fish and great service. Don't forget to check out the patio on a nice day and BYOB!
Fantastic sushi with an awesome outdoor patio! Also BYOB, which is a cool and cost savings idea.
Very good quality fish! Always great service and a  friendly staff. Highly recommended.
Really tasty signature rolls. My friend said the nigiri was delicious too. Too loud for my taste - had to shout to make myself heard.
Best sushi in Noble Square / Wicker Park

We walked in one hr before they were closing and it was almost as if we were asking for handouts because they barely wanted to serve us. Not only did they rush to take our order but we weren't even finished eating when the waitress was rudely reaching over as I was still eating trying to take my plate off the table. There was still 20 minutes left for them to close and not once did they come ask if we needed anything, not even after we were the only customers in the restaurant. Never going back.
Good sushi for the price. 20% off after 9pm.
Excellent!! This is my favorite BYOB sushi place in town and very reasonably priced. Sashimi platter is outstanding as well as all food I've ordered. Cannot wait for the patio to be open. Thank you!
Byob and specials. Love this place and their Rolls!
Always great -
Can you give zero stars? This place wait is terrible along with their response time. Then it may just be towards me. I dont think their to happy when other races enter their establishment

The food tasted pretty good, but everything else was terrible. The table was so dirty multiple people got stains on there clothes. The entrees came out over a period of 35 min. Two people had there food totally forgotten about and one person had their order wrong. The only time our water was filled was when we first sat down.  The bathroom was filthy and there was trash all over the floor of the entire restaurant.  All together, it was a really really bad experience.

Two of my friends got stains on their dresses from the unclean table, there was old rice stuck to my chop sticks, the orders weren't correct, the service was slow and came in a batch fashion instead of simultaneously.  Still, there was complimentary food on the house. The food was tasty. Most of all, the staff was very courteous and genuinely apologetic, so I can't be too harsh.

The sushi is really good, but sometimes the rice is a little hard rather than sticky. I would avoid the maki as a lot of them have this overly sweet sauce or plain Sriracha. The atmosphere was nice and the service was excellent.
Don't Overlook This BYOB Sushi Spot!  Huge Menu and Great House Rolls!
Slowest people in the world.

Amazing menu and the guy who runs the front is super cool. BYOB makes it one of the best. So affordable and superb quality sushi. Sad to share as I don't want it to get crowded. They do take reservations which is recommended.
GREAT food!  Rolls melt in your mouth. Good music,.
Great sushi! Amazing eel Temaki!!
Great sushi great price!
Highly recommend the sashimi platter. Amazingly fresh sushi and great presentation.
Excellent sushi, excellent sauce.
Love the rolls here! Fresh and Delish!

Omg! The sushi is incredible. We had tons of dishes but what stood out most was the dragon and the best was the sea monster. Waitress was a little non-existent near the end but this rating is for the food.
Great sushi highly recommend the spicy miso soup and fresh wasabi.
fresh wasabi.
Best sushi ever.  Shitaki mushroom tempura melts in your mouth!  We brought $10 bottle of wine and spent $36 on food...... Best Valentine's Day ever!
Loved the setting, the decor, service and food. One of my go to sushi shops in Chicago.
Good sushi. BYOB. Awesome patio.

The first time I came here, I wasn't too impressed since my friend got a really dry roll with just bonita flakes (avoid this one if you can!). This time, I was very impressed by my midnight sundae sushi! It was incredible. The fish on top was very fresh and tender and I liked how the sauce was salty yet sweet at the same time.  The space is really tight and I really think they should expand. The waitresses were squeezing past us since the space is just so bad for a restaurant. It's also BYOB and you can get free sweet potato tempura if you check in!

The fish was fresh, but everything else was disappointing. The sushi rice was mushy and not well-seasoned, the carpaccio appetizer was drenched in sweet sauce, and the service was slow, despite most of the restaurant being empty on a Saturday night at 7 pm. As for ambiance, it felt like every other pan-Asian ever: bad dance music, dim lighting, and not much else. Skip it.

Seadog is always awesome. I have dined in and carried out too many times to count over the past 8 years. Their service is great, atmosphere great, and most importantly the sushi is phenomenal. I highly recommend it to all my friends and neighbors and look forward to my next order!
Seadog is my favorite spot for sushi!  It can get crowded in the restaurant, but the food is very fresh and so delicious.  Also, in the summer the back deck is a great spot to eat outside.

cute small joint. all their specials are good and their deserts are ridic good! its it BYOB which akes it good for small groups. lighting is dim for first dates. parking is easy on division anytime of day.
BYOB!!!  Have been coming here for years and the patio garden is awesome!

I had high expectations for Seadog, especially with the Michelin recommendation being prominently mentioned on their web site and menu. Unfortunately, my experiences tonight make me wonder how they achieved it. The appetizers and salads were quite tasty, but the main courses and overall experience were not good at all.  We learned upon arriving that they will not seat parties over 4 outside, so despite there being plenty of room, we weren't allowed to put two tables together. Our waitress did not speak English very well, so it was hard to get more information on the various dishes, and we had to repeat our requests to other staff so we would get what we needed.  Dinner was horrible, they forgot to make the food for two of our party, and the food that did come out was too salty to eat. They did not seem to care that the food was largely uneaten, and charged us full price for everything we did not eat. I definitely will not be going back there again.
A perfect sushi spot with BYOB! Amazing tuna rolls and great hidden spot. Quality food, good location and great place to bring a date.
Cant beat BYOB.  The sushi rolls were creative and tasty.  Really enjoyed the takoyaki.  Good local sushi joint.  Definitely the best sushi in noble square.  If you are in the area, hit it up
BYOB.  Great traditional and inventive sushi.  Good for big groups and a casual date.  Also the patio is great in the summer.

Went here for lunch with my sister. We were there between 4-6, so it wasn't busy. Staff was super friendly and and the sushi was tasty, though not quite up there... Restaurant is smallish, but has a cool ambient feel.
The best sushi in Chicago with Great service and Great prices. It is BYOB and has a great Wicker Park neighborhood feel with a nice outdoor area as well.

the place is great environment, you can sit at the sushi bar and an octopus may look at you straight in the eye. you can bring you own drink to the bar and they'll nicely serve for you. the sushi is awesome and my favorite is grilled scallop, love love it. the price is little higher than nori, which is also a japanese restaurant located in wicker park area.

Great sushi at a totally reasonable price... try the escolar! Byob which is awesome. Atmosphere is intimate, good for a dates. Candle lit and enjoyable, definitely hit this spot when you are in Bucktown.

Seadog is the best sushi in the city.  Even better, it's BYOB.  It gets very busy on the weekend, so call ahead for a reservation.  Be sure to try the sweet pototo roll.  We also had the chef's recco which was superb (although I don't remember what it was).

Look out Coast Sushi, this place is a hit! It's my new favorite sushi BYOB in the city. The back patio in the summer is incredible... too bad we're going into the winter now. Guess I'll have to count down to the spring, but that won't stop me from enjoying these delicious rolls.
Seadog is my favorite sushi restaurant.  Their patio is gorgeous, their fish is the best in the city, and the Secret Garden Vegetarian Roll is a foodgasm.
The service is great and the sushi is AMAZING. I crave this place. Only thing is if you go on the weekends it can get pretty loud inside. The patio in the back is key.
Cozy, neighborhood BYOB sushi joint. The fish is always fresh and well-prepared. The spicy miso hits the spot.

Seadog is great sushi in a warm, modern atmosphere without being pretentious.  The quality of the fish is great at a reasonable price and the staff is very friendly.  On weekends the BYOB crowd starts getting their party on after around 9ish which makes it a great place to kick off a night out.
